5","about 1075":"omkring 1075","1050":"1050","Croft, Herefordshire, England":"Croft, Herefordshire, England","Leominster, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Leominster, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","Hereford, Herefordshire, England":"Hereford, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Frankrig","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1026–1098":"1026–1098","1050–Female":"1050–Overleden","1075–Male":"1075–Overleden","1090–1149":"1090–1149","1090–Male":"1090–Overleden","1035–1099":"1035–1099","1090":"1090","1149":"1149","1026":"1026","Abt. 1090":"circa 1090","1035":"1035","1099":"1099","1098":"1098","1086":"1086","1075":"1075","about 1075":"circa 1075","1050":"1050","Croft, Herefordshire, England":"Croft, Herefordshire, England","Leominster, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Leominster, Herefordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Hereford, Herefordshire, England":"Hereford, Herefordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Frankrijk","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1026–1098":"1026–1098","1050–Female":"1050–Deceased","1075–Male":"1075–Deceased","1090–1149":"1090–1149","1090–Male":"1090–Deceased","1035–1099":"1035–1099","1090":"1090","1149":"1149","1026":"1026","Abt. 1090":"about 1090","1035":"1035","1099":"1099","1098":"1098","1086":"1086","1075":"1075","about 1075":"about 1075","1050":"1050","Croft, Herefordshire, England":"Croft, Herefordshire, England","Leominster, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Leominster, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","Hereford, Herefordshire, England":"Hereford, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","Normandy, France":"Normandy, France","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Croft","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of several places, for example in Lincolnshire, Lancashire, Herefordshire, and North Yorkshire, all named with Old English <i>croft</i> ‘small arable enclosure (normally adjoining a house)’, or a topographic name for someone who lived by a croft, from Middle English <i>croft</i>.","English: possibly in some cases a variant of   Craft   2.","Americanized form of German, Danish, Swedish, or Jewish   Kraft  . Compare   Kroft   and   Craft  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Craft","meanings":["English: nickname from Middle English <i>craft</i> ‘skillful, clever, learned’.","English: habitational name from Croft in Leicestershire. See also   Croft  .","Americanized form of German, Danish, Swedish, or Jewish   Kraft  . See also   Croft  ."]},{"name":"Crate","meanings":["English (Hampshire and Surrey): from Middle English <i>crate</i> ‘hurdle, basket’, or occasionally perhaps from <i>crete</i> ‘cradle’, probably applied as a metonymic occupational name for a maker of such articles. Alternatively, sometimes perhaps a variant of   Croft   1."]},{"name":"Crofts","meanings":["English: variant of   Croft  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Groft","meanings":["English: perhaps an altered form of   Croft  ."]}]},{"name":"Bernard","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>ber(n)</i> ‘bear’ + <i>hard</i> ‘hardy, brave, strong’. This was the name of three famous medieval churchmen:  St Bernard  of Menthon (  923–1008 ), founder of a hospice on each of the Alpine passes named after him; the monastic reformer  St Bernard  of Clairvaux (  1090–1153 ); and the scholastic philosopher  Bernard  of Chartres. It was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England. A native Old English form, <i>Beornheard</i>, was superseded by the Norman form."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Bernard de Croft was born in 1026, in Normandy, France as the son of (Knight Of Sepulchre) Jasper De Croft. He married Catherine Taylor. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died in 1098, in Leominster, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 72."},"et":{"1026–1098":"1026–1098","1050–Female":"1050–Surnud","1075–Male":"1075–Surnud","1090–1149":"1090–1149","1090–Male":"1090–Surnud","1035–1099":"1035–1099","1090":"1090","1149":"1149","1026":"1026","Abt. 1090":"umbes 1090","1035":"1035","1099":"1099","1098":"1098","1086":"1086","1075":"1075","about 1075":"umbes 1075","1050":"1050","Croft, Herefordshire, England":"Croft, Herefordshire, England","Leominster, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Leominster, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hereford, Herefordshire, England":"Hereford, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1026–1098":"1026–1098","1050–Female":"1050–Kuollut","1075–Male":"1075–Kuollut","1090–1149":"1090–1149","1090–Male":"1090–Kuollut","1035–1099":"1035–1099","1090":"1090","1149":"1149","1026":"1026","Abt. 1090":"noin 1090","1035":"1035","1099":"1099","1098":"1098","1086":"1086","1075":"1075","about 1075":"noin 1075","1050":"1050","Croft, Herefordshire, Engl